MultiPixel Branding & Logo Usage Guide
Version 1.0 — Relimintor (Raptor4 / MultiPixel)

1. PURPOSE
This document defines how MultiPixel branding may be used by servers, mod
creators, content creators, and community members.

2. PROTECTED BRAND ELEMENTS
The following names and marks are protected:
• “MultiPixel”
• “Relimintor”
• “Raptor4”
• “Raptor4mc”
• MultiPixel logos, icons, and visual identity

3. GENERAL RULES
a. Branding may NOT be used without explicit written approval.
b. Branding may NOT be altered, recolored, distorted, or remixed.
c. Branding may NOT be used in:
   • domain names
   • social media handles
   • server names
   • community names
   • mod names
   unless explicitly approved.

4. UNOFFICIAL LABELING
a. Unofficial servers must display:
   “Unofficial MultiPixel Server”
b. Unofficial mods must display:
   “Unofficial MultiPixel Mod”

5. PROHIBITED USES
Branding may NOT be used:
• to imply partnership or endorsement
• in political content (unless approved)
• in adult or unsafe content
• in misleading or fraudulent contexts
• in competing games or engines
• in AI training or generation

6. CONTENT CREATION
Allowed:
• Gameplay videos
• Reviews
• Commentary
• Tutorials

Not allowed:
• Using logos in thumbnails without approval
• Using branding to impersonate staff

7. ENFORCEMENT
Violations may result in:
• removal of content
• server bans
• legal action
• DMCA takedowns
